  "commentary": "With SPX at 6756.97 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6750 (-11.8B) and positive gamma at 6775 (+7.4B), dealers are in active hedging mode as we've just broken through key levels with a 75.6% GEX surge detected. In this BREAKOUT regime, dealers are short gamma and will be buying this move higher, creating momentum amplification as we approach the 6775 resistance where they'll start selling to hedge their long delta exposure. The tight 25-point range between max negative (6750) and max positive (6775) gamma creates a critical battleground - a break below 6750 triggers dealer buying that could accelerate downside, while a push through 6775 faces heavy dealer selling pressure.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile whipsaw action between 6750 and 6775 with potential for explosive moves on either breakout.",
